name: Olivia Hooker
description: She was the last known survivor of the Tulsa race riots of 1921, and the first African-American woman to enter the U.S. Coast Guard in February 1945

name: Katharine Johnson
description: Calculated the orbital mechanics of the first and subsequent U.S. manned spaceflights for NASA

name: Rhetaugh Graves Dumas
description: Said to have been the first nurse to use the scientific method to conduct experiments that evaluated nursing practices, and the first woman or African American deputy director of the NIMH

name: Mae C. Jemison
description: First African American woman to travel in space when she went into orbit aboard the Space Shuttle Endeavour on September 12, 1992

name: Mary Jackson
description: In 1958, became NASA's first black female engineer and had earned the most senior engineering title available of her time.
